    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-08-03</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-09-27T17:07:16Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends title XIX (Medicaid) of the Social Security Act, as amended by the U.S. Troop Readiness, Veterans' Care, Katrina Recovery, and Iraq Accountability Appropriations Act, 2007, to: (1) apply the required use of tamper-resistant prescription pads under the Medicaid Program at first only to Controlled Substances Act schedule II narcotic drugs prescribed after September 30, 2007; and (2) delay the application of the requirement to other covered outpatient prescription drugs until after March 31, 2009.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Patient and Pharmacy Protection Act of 2007</title>
